right now.

00:09.601 --> 00:12.952
Just... loose in the wild.

00:13.083 --> 00:14.824
Hiya!

00:14.954 --> 00:16.739
[Miles] So as you can see,
I am in jail.

00:16.826 --> 00:18.175
Ashley decided
she couldn't handle

00:18.305 --> 00:19.785
telling Sean
where I was right away,

00:19.916 --> 00:21.047
so she told him
I was doing a moving job.

00:21.178 --> 00:22.832
To Montana.

00:22.962 --> 00:24.486
[Miles] I'm gonna be here
for years,

00:24.616 --> 00:26.313
and she can't hold off
his questions anymore.

00:26.444 --> 00:28.141
How do you tell a six-year-old
his dad won't be home?

00:29.969 --> 00:32.668
Okay, kid.
What's it gonna be today?

00:32.798 --> 00:35.888
Princess and the Frog?
The Wiz?

00:36.019 --> 00:38.325
Akeelah and the Bee?
Cool Runnings?

00:38.456 --> 00:40.676
I wanna watch Paddington 2.

00:40.806 --> 00:42.155
Whodington what?

00:44.941 --> 00:45.811
Uh--

00:47.465 --> 00:49.728
It's about a British bear?

00:49.859 --> 00:51.251
Yeah.

00:51.382 --> 00:52.644
Don't you wanna watch
a Black movie?

00:52.775 --> 00:54.690
What's a Black movie?

00:54.820 --> 00:57.344
A movie with people
Black like you.

00:57.475 --> 00:58.911
What color you think
you are, Sean?

00:59.042 --> 01:00.696
Honey brown.

01:03.655 --> 01:05.657
Fuck.

01:05.788 --> 01:08.530
[dramatic music plays]

01:08.704 --> 01:11.446
♪ ♪

01:17.408 --> 01:19.410
Not everything
is black and white,

01:19.541 --> 01:21.586
all good or all bad.

01:21.717 --> 01:23.458
Some things are both--

01:23.545 --> 01:25.460
the way you can be
both happy and sad.

01:27.200 --> 01:29.942
Some things we're told
are bad are good,

01:30.073 --> 01:32.989
and some things we're sold
as good are bad.

01:33.119 --> 01:34.904
And some things change

01:35.034 --> 01:38.342
depending on
where you choose to stand.

01:38.473 --> 01:40.692
Life is about how you choose
to see the truth at hand.

01:42.389 --> 01:44.696
And the truth isn't planned,
isn't clean.

01:44.827 --> 01:47.307
It's a crapshoot
of Mom and Dad's moves

01:47.394 --> 01:48.613
falling off a moving van.

01:48.700 --> 01:50.528
It's...

01:50.659 --> 01:52.399
it's not a movie, Sean.

01:52.530 --> 01:55.185
It's a piece of music
in and out of tune.

01:55.315 --> 01:57.317
It's an unruly dance. It's a--

01:57.448 --> 01:59.232
Bitch, what the fuck
are you talking about?

01:59.363 --> 02:00.930
No, mm-mm, don't say that.

02:01.060 --> 02:02.714
You need to just tell him
his dad's in jail.

02:02.845 --> 02:05.064
Don't make
a goddamn dance analogy.

02:05.195 --> 02:07.632
I'm just trying to figure out
the right way to tell him.

02:07.763 --> 02:09.591
He's gonna be so scared,

02:09.721 --> 02:11.506
and I don't want him to think
his dad is a bad person.

02:11.636 --> 02:14.509
Oh, honey, come on. I know.
It's a lot.

02:14.639 --> 02:16.032
Look, it's slow today.

02:16.162 --> 02:17.947
We're at, like, 30% capacity,

02:18.077 --> 02:20.471
and I'm sure I can handle
any requests that come down,

02:20.602 --> 02:23.213
and you seem...

02:23.343 --> 02:25.824
in shambles,
let's just say that.

02:25.955 --> 02:27.739
You know, why don't you
take off early

02:27.870 --> 02:30.176
and take some time to reword
that speech a bit better?

02:30.263 --> 02:31.047
Spend some time
with your thoughts.

02:36.182 --> 02:38.620
And how will you spend the day
with your thought?

02:38.707 --> 02:40.535
I wanna smoke.

02:40.665 --> 02:42.493
Ooh, I thought we were
cutting back on that, baby.

02:42.624 --> 02:44.277
No, I mean smoke.

02:44.408 --> 02:48.586
Ooh, this is a nice-ass coat.

02:48.717 --> 02:50.501
I wanna go for a walk.

02:50.632 --> 02:51.807
In nature, please.

02:54.679 --> 02:56.246
And it's a date.

02:58.030 --> 02:59.902
-I just do what I'm told.
-[Ashley] Mm-hmm.

03:00.032 --> 03:02.774
[soft music plays]

03:02.948 --> 03:05.821
